node.title: 'We've got her': Police release emotional audio recording of moment little girl found
node.alt: Cleo Smith carried by police officer
node.description: Police release an emotional audio recording of the moment they burst into a house in the WA coastal town of Carnarvon and found missing four-year-old Cleo Smith.
node.content: ["Police have released an emotional\u00a0audio recording of the moment they burst into a house in the WA coastal town of Carnarvon\u00a0and found missing four-year-old Cleo Smith sitting on the floor of a bedroom.", "\"We've got her. We've got her,\" an\u00a0officer is heard to say.", "\"Hey bubby,\" another says.", "\"Come here.", "\"I've got you bubby,\" the first officer says. What's your name?", "When there is no immediate response, he asks again: \"What's your name sweetheart?\"", "\"M-My name is Cleo,\" the little girl says in a trembling voice.", "\"Your name is Cleo,\" the officer tells her, the relief in his voice obvious.", "\"You're alright, bubby.\""]
